You are working on Katana Fork — a local Anvil fork of Katana Network with a Next.js frontend for testing KAT staking, voting, and vault operations.

## Tech stack
- Foundry (Solidity 0.8.24) for smart contract tests
- Next.js 16 + React 19 + TypeScript for frontend
- wagmi v2 + viem for chain interaction
- Tailwind CSS v4 with custom ink/katana theme

## Key files
- `foundry/src/KatanaConfig.sol` — All contract addresses and constants
- `foundry/test/Base.t.sol` — Test harness (extend KatanaForkTest)
- `frontend/src/config/abis.ts` — Contract ABIs
- `frontend/src/config/contracts.ts` — Contract addresses
- `frontend/src/app/globals.css` — Theme (ink-* dark, katana-* blue accent)
- `frontend/src/lib/format.ts` — fmtEther() for 4-decimal display

## Rules
- Use `fmtEther()` for display values, raw `formatEther()` only for input MAX buttons
- Exit queue params (cooldown, fees) must be read from chain, never hardcoded
- Use `ink-*` colors for backgrounds/text, `katana-*` for brand accent, `emerald-*` only for success
- Buttons use rounded-full (pill shape): btn-primary, btn-secondary, btn-danger
- Forge tests: extend KatanaForkTest, use _advancePastMinLock() before beginWithdrawal
- After beginWithdrawal, NFT is in escrow — use ExitQueue.queue(tokenId) not ownedTokens()
- Voting requires self-delegation via IVotesAdapter.delegate(address)
- Merge (VotingEscrow.merge) does NOT need NFT approval — works across epochs, while voting
- Split (VotingEscrow.split) — both resulting NFTs must have >= minDeposit (0.5 KAT)

## Chain
- Katana mainnet RPC: https://rpc.katana.network
- Local fork: http://127.0.0.1:8545
- Chain ID: 747474

## Commands
- `make fork` — Start Anvil fork at latest block
- `make test` — Run 19 forge tests
- `make dev` — Start frontend dev server
- `make warp DAYS=N` — Fast-forward fork time
